Lifemate Group has unveiled new products into Nigeria’s markets to meet the basic needs of Nigerians, the company’s partners in the furniture industry as well as save the country from the cost of importing them from abroad. The Whole Sales Department Manager, Anas Khuwias, during the unveiling at the company’s office in Mowe, Ogun State, said the new products were outdoor furniture; solid wood, wrought iron, Sofa products and customized mattress. Kuwait added that the products were not common in Nigeria’s market and that they were innovated to make life better for Nigerians. “Lifemate is the largest manufacturer of outdoor products in Nigeria. Our craftsmanship and styles of rattan weaving closely follow the development of the international outdoor furniture industry. “And the latest technology has been introduced into Nigeria. Therefore, you can see many unique styles and colours. There are more new products to introduce to you every year,” he said. The whole sales supervisor, Mark Otobo, said the company produced the unique products to avoid the importation cost, the stress of travelling out of the country to get good deals and to sell unique goods at affordable rates. He added that Lifemate Group has commissioned a new branch at Ojo-Alaba.